<div class="center">
	<b>Privacy policy of the yunNet project.</b>
</div>
<br>
<div>
	<b>1. General Provisions.</b>
	<p>1.1. From now on, yunNet. - then the Project, and the site visitor - then the User agrees with the privacy policy while using this resource. Project rules - a number of restrictions necessary for comfortable interaction between the participants - hereinafter referred to as the Rules. The Project Administration - a number of Users required to moderate the Project - hereinafter referred to as the Owners.</p>
	<p>1.2. The privacy policy can be updated with partial notification of the User (if the changes relate to the protection of personal data) or without notifying the latter.</p>
	<br>
	<b>2. Copyright of the Project</b>
	<p>2.1. The default theme "Default theme" and the dark theme of the Project "Dark theme" belong to the Project. Distribution is possible <b>only within the Project.</b></p>
	<p>2.2. The general design concept remains owned by the Project and cannot be copied / transferred without the permission of the Project owners.</p>
	<p>2.2. Any innovations implemented by the developers of the Project are also protected by copyright and cannot be extended outside the Project.</p>
	<p>2.2. The Project Owners are not responsible for the content published by the Users in places inaccessible to the Administration (private messages, private records, etc.))</p>
	<p>2.3. Any public content can be removed if it violates the copyright of other resources, Users, etc.</p>
	<br>
	<b>3. Copyright of the User</b>
	<p>3.1. Any content (posts, comments, messages, etc.) published by the User automatically belongs to the User himself, copyright and access to the content is limited by him.</p>
	<p>3.2. The user fully owns such information as: Main photo of the page, Short link to the page, Accounts-bots</p>
	<p>3.3. Posts left on the wall of another User also give him the copyright for this post.</p>
	<p>3.4. The records left on the User's personal page or his Bot Account are available to other users until they are deleted or hidden. This allows other Users to perform various actions with the records (commenting, rating, etc.)</p>
	<br>
	<b>4. Protection of personal data</b>
	<p>4.1. By registering or authorizing on the Project, the User automatically agrees with the Rules of the Project and the privacy policy.</p>
	<p>4.2. The Project Owners do not have any access to such personal data of the User as: Account passwords, Email address, Messages, Conversations, Dialogues of Accounts-Bots, Phone number. This data cannot be passed on to third parties or viewed in any way.</p>
	<p>4.3. Other Users and guests of the Project have access to such personal information as: Name, Surname, Gender. Data such as: Age, City, etc. can be hidden by the User himself.</p>
	<p>4.4. The personal data mentioned above are necessary for the correct operation of the service and cannot be published anywhere without the knowledge of the User.</p>
	<br>
	<b>5. Ownership</b>
	<p>5.1. Each element of the interface, API methods, Applications, Accounts and other elements of the site belong exclusively to the Owners of the Project or the yunNet site.</p>
</div>
